# Sibling .dockerignore for test/dev/vunnel.Dockerfile.
#
# When this Dockerfile is built with $VUNNEL_PATH as the context (so the
# COPY . /src step sees the vunnel source tree), Docker's default lookup
# would otherwise pick vunnel's repo-local .dockerignore — which is tuned for
# the release image and excludes everything except /dist. That would leave us
# with no source to install. BuildKit picks the <Dockerfile-name>.dockerignore
# in the same directory as the Dockerfile when -f is used, so this file wins.
#
# We allow source by default and only exclude caches / local state that would
# bloat the image without affecting the install.
.git/
.venv/
.cache/
.pytest_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.tool/
build/
dist/
htmlcov/
data/
*.pyc
__pycache__/
